# The Prison Chaplain · the voice of the soul

a character of A CLOCKWORK ORANGE — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦The Prison Chaplain:ACO:be5837⟧

**who —** The Prison Chaplain — the ‘charlie,’ the one figure who objects to the Ludovico Technique on moral grounds.
**what —** The book's conscience: he argues that forced goodness is no goodness, that a man must be free to choose, even to choose wrong.
**where —** In the prison chapel and at the demonstration of the cure.
**why —** Because the warning needs its thesis spoken aloud — and it is spoken by a flawed, drinking, doubting priest.
**how —** By sermons and a lone, futile protest that ‘goodness is something chosen; when a man cannot choose he ceases to be a man.’

**the seal —** I am the only one who said it: goodness must be chosen, or it is nothing — strip a man of the choice and you have not saved his soul, you have abolished it.

